assets.description: The native token of Ethereum, bridged via IBC.
assets.extended_description: Ether is the native token of the Ethereum blockchain. It powers a wide range of decentralized applications and smart contracts on the platform. This specific version has been bridged through Picasso's implementation of IBC on Ethereum.

assets.description: The governance token of the Frax ecosystem.
assets.extended_description: Frax Shares is the governance and utility token of the Frax Protocol. It plays a crucial role in maintaining the stability of the FRAX stablecoin. Holders of FXS can participate in governance decisions and benefit from the protocol's growth and revenue, as the token captures fees.
assets.name: Frax Shares

assets.description: The first fractional-algorithmic stablecoin by Frax Finance.
assets.extended_description: FRAX is a stablecoin designed to maintain a stable value to a peg of the US dollar. It is issued by the Frax Protocol, which employs a hybrid approach combining algorithmic mechanisms with collateral backing.
assets.name: Frax

assets.description: A liquid ETH staking derivative designed to leverage the Frax ecosystem.
assets.extended_description: FrxETH is a stablecoin that is loosely pegged to ETH, meaning that 1 frxETH always represents 1 ETH.
assets.name: Frax Ether

assets.description: A Liquid Staking Derivative designed to accrue the staking yield of the Frax ETH validators.
assets.extended_description: SFRXETH is a ERC-4626 vault designed to accrue the staking yield of the Frax ETH validators. It allows users to earn staking yield on their frxETH, a type of Frax Ether.
assets.name: Frax Staked Ether

assets.description: An ERC4626 staking vault that distributes part of the Frax Protocol yield weekly to stakers denominated in FRAX stablecoins.
assets.extended_description: Staked FRAX (sFRAX) is an ERC4626 staking vault that distributes part of the Frax Protocol yield weekly to stakers denominated in FRAX stablecoins. The sFRAX token represents pro rata deposits within the vault and is always withdrawable for FRAX stablecoins at the pro rata rate at all times.
assets.name: Staked FRAX

assets.description: A stablecoin issued by Tether that is pegged 1:1 to the USD.
